      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 standard test protocol followed at both laboratories. Crosshead displacement rate 5 mm/min, ambient temperature 23±2°C, calibrated load cells (NIST-traceable). However, only a single test condition (standard F1717 configuration) was evaluated; no variation in loading rate, temperature range, or fixture orientation was explored. This limits the breadth of validation coverage to the nominal COU condition only. Achieved level 2 falls short of required level 3 for this factor; shortfall addressed in decision record offset rationale.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
