      "name": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) directly correspond to the regulatory decision criteria for pedicle screw mechanical performance per FDA guidance and ASTM F1717. Stiffness characterizes immediate post-operative stability; yield force captures failure onset relevant to revision surgery risk; force at 40 mm characterizes post-yield energy absorption. Clinical relevance documented with reference to FDA guidance document for spinal implants. Achieved level 3.",
